---------------------------------------------
I. Web interface:

1) Run server on default port 8080* 

 windows:
	C:\ais> server
	(or just double-click on server.bat)
 unix:
    $ . server.sh 
        or
    $ sh server
        or
    $ chmod u+x server; ./server.sh

2) Open browser on http://localhost:8080


---------------------------------------------
II. command-line interface:

 windows:
    C:\ais> ais --help
 unix:
    $ ./ais --help

---------------------------------------------
III. java native GUI (swing) client:

 windows:
    C:\ais> swing (or double-click on swing.bat)
 unix:
    $ ./swing
---------------------------------------------
IV. piping an output from a program to AIS (under Unix only):

	$ cat dump.out | ./ais
		or
	$ echo "/etc/samba/smb.conf samba config" | ais
---------------------------------------------
V. automatic indexing of C:\ drive under Windows, from command-line 
(can be put under cron-like utility):
	C:\ais> ais -d C:/

 This took 4 hours for indexing 98G of files on remote drive at my work
 (mostly text, word end excel docs etc) and 2.5 hours - for indexing 
 local workstation (40G of files, mostly windows, binaries).
 Incremental runs took 30 minutes in 1st case, and 20 minutes - in the 
 second one.


	